01/03/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu said Monday (28 February) that his country would no longer accept the label of a corrupt country and demanded that the West support any future allegations by naming names. 
Following a meeting of the Supreme Defence Council that focused on corruption, Basescu declared that concrete evidence would help enhance measures undertaken against corruption.
In other news, EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn opened a series of meetings in Bucharest on Monday and urged the government to boost efforts to fulfil set EU-integration reforms. 
Rehn said Bucharest has no time to lose, as the clock is ticking and the meeting of deadlines is crucial. 
(Rompres, Nine o'clock, Ziarul financiar, Cotidianul - 01/03/05)
